          "icon": "beach",
          "title": {
            "en": "Does Corniglia have a beach?"
          },
          "description": {
            "en": "No direct beach access. It's the only Cinque Terre village without a beach. Take train to Vernazza or Manarola."
          }
        },
        {
          "icon": "crowd",
          "title": {
            "en": "Is Corniglia crowded?"
          },
          "description": {
            "en": "Least crowded of all five villages. The staircase deters many tourists. Most authentic local atmosphere."
          }
        },
        {
          "icon": "time",
          "title": {
            "en": "How long to spend in Corniglia?"
          },
          "description": {
            "en": "2-3 hours to see highlights. Half day with lunch. Full day if hiking or staying overnight."
          }
